The paper deals with defect tracking systems and the analysis of duplicate defect reports in open source software projects. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also involves data mining and information retrieval techniques to capture the inter-relationships among duplicate defects, which could potentially fall under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper may involve aspects of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) since defects in software can have security implications and affect the functioning of physical systems.
